items.name: Alyssa Milano LoRA
items.description:
A Stable Diffusion LoRA profile based on Alyssa Milano.

Very annoying how following the same method for each Lora can give amazing results most of the time and then really hit and miss results with another, this is one of the latter, can give amazing renders but may take a few attempts.

Place it in "stable-diffusion-webui\extensions\sd-webui-additional-networks\models\lora" folder in Automatic1111 WebUI root folder.

Made using kohya-ss so make sure to have that extension installed!

In txt2img, under "Additional Networks", select "Enable" and under Model 1 select "Alyssa Milano" and assign a weight between 0.3-0.7 (feel free to experiment!). In the prompt text window use "Alyssa Milano" within your prompt to generate images.

Embed has been trained on Stable Diffusion 1.5 model.

I Recommend the model

https://civitai.com/models/4922/grapelikedreamfruit - Gives amazing realistic renders.

items.name: Ganyu (Genshin Impact) - Realistic + Anime - LoRA
items.description:
Ganyu (Genshin Impact) - Realistic + Anime - LoRA

Making models can be expensive. Do you like what I do? Consider supporting me on Patreon üÖøÔ∏è or feel free to buy me a coffee ‚òï

I know that there are already many Ganyu LoRA's, however I wanted to test a new technique using NeverEnding Dream (NED) as a base for training to basically turn an anime character into a real one. This is not trained on cosplay images but just on about 300 Ganyu fanarts.

It's flexible enough to make her in any style (realistic or anime, with a bit of help from style loras for a more dramatic effect) and any outfit and hairstyle. Please check the examples.

Triggers with ganyu \(genshin impact\) usually at weight 1 but might require tuning based on the model you're using it on (sometimes I used 1.2, sometimes 0.65). Works great on NeverEnding Dream and with Korean/Japanese likeness loras, or on any anime model out there.

Please enjoy and consider supporting me.

How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight according to the instructions (by default it's :1)

items.name: Nicola Cavanis
items.description:
Nicola Cavanis is a German model and social media influencer with more than 1M followers on Instagram.

This TI has been updated! Please check the "About this version" section for more info.

Note: Really sorry for updating the TI again so soon, but I think the previous version had some flaws that I hope this new one (3.1) will address.

130-step TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings.

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Do you have a specific idea for a TI in mind? Visit my website and let me know.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (nicol4c4:0.99), a woman as a movie star, modelshoot style, (extremely detailed CG unity 8k wallpaper), photo of the most beautiful artwork in the world, professional majestic oil painting by Ed Blinkey, Atey Ghailan, Studio Ghibli, by Jeremy Mann, Greg Manchess, Antonio Moro, trending on ArtStation, trending on CGSociety, Intricate, High Detail, Sharp focus, dramatic, photorealistic painting art by midjourney and greg rutkowski, (white turtleneck top:1.2), ((movie premiere)), (long skirt), ((standing near a movie theater)), ((paparazzi in the background)), (looking at viewer:1.2), (detailed pupils:1.3), ((closeup portrait:1.1))"

It doesn't seem to have had a negative impact, so I guess perhaps I'm wrong about how important that part is. In the end, it seems the quality of the images is, by far, the most important thing.

800 steps for this TI. I've checked previous steps and they weren't as accurate, so I'll settle for this one, which in my opinion looks very good. It also gets rid of the saturation that was probably the main issue with the previous version. My settings haven't changed.

Get your roasted reptiles ready because it is time for Chloe!

The prompt "chloe (fire emblem)" or better yet "chloe \(fire emblem\)" is used to trigger this one. Escaping the parentheses helps avoid emphasizing "fire emblem" specifically in UIs like Automatic1111 and, I've noticed, seems to be good practice for most similar booru tags

items.name: Crosskemono(furry_model&human_model)
items.description:
The sample images are generated by my friend "ËÅñËÅñËÅñ‰πü" -> his PIXIV page.

I have set my models forbidden to be used for commercial purposes, so please report to me if you find anyone using my models for commercial purposes.

"I would like to express my gratitude to Philip_ovo for helping me publish the model on Furry Diffusion Discord. If possible, please also support the Lora model MJFurryLora And NJFurryLora created by Philip_ovo."


This English version of the description has been modified based on the translation by marbrdf on ChatGPT.

This model is designed to generate kemono-style furry using booru tags and can generate human-like figures without decreasing the quality of the output. The model is designed to produce images without blurring the background.

See the model description for more details.

  • Models are named alphabetically based on the order in which they were uploaded, and the later models are not necessarily better. Choose Model A, B, C, D, E, F or G based on your needs. This is similar to orange and 7th, and you can intuitively compare them with reference images to see the differences.

  • If you only want to use a short prompt without adjusting the weights and without using the kemono-style Hypernetwork or Lora to generate kemono, choose Model B.

  • If you have a basic prompt foundation and can adjust the weights but do not want to use the kemono-style Hypernetwork or Lora to generate kemono, choose Model D.

  • If you want a very different style and can accept using the kemono-style Hypernetwork or Lora to generate kemono, choose Model C.

  • If you want to generate attractive human-like figures and kemono-style furry that are close to the current mainstream anime style, and can accept using the kemono-style Hypernetwork or Lora to generate kemono, choose Model A.

  • If you are looking for a more realistic texture similar to AOM2 or AOM3, and can accept not using the kemono-style Hypernetwork or Lora to generate kemono with a more realistic painting style, then choose Model F.

  • If you want clear lines and celluloid-style coloring, and are willing to accept that the characters generated by Model E may appear very young and petite, then choose Model E.

  • If you are looking for a highly impasto coloring style and incredibly detailed and accurate scenes with a rich and colorful palette, and are willing to accept that the generated kemono poses in Model G may have a more fleshy feel, such as a more visible navel, then choose Model G. Please note that this model requires the use of kemono-style Hypernetwork or Lora to generate kemono, as otherwise, unnecessary human ears and incorrect animal noses may be generated.

This series of models combines five Lora styles I trained myself with five kemono-style furry Lorastyles in a hierarchical U-net model that I repeatedly fine-tuned through layer merging.

Like Counterfeit and Pastel, this model uses a hierarchical U-net model combined with Lora. However, because it includes two completely different species with different body structures, humans and kemono furry, in the merging process, its stability is not as good as that of a general model.

The models used in the process include but are not limited to the Anything series, Orange series, Pastel+ (Yohan series), Counterfeit series, and 7th series, totaling more than 50 models combined, plus my own personal Lora model, so I cannot share the recipe.

Although this series of models can generate NSFW content, it is recommended to use any Lora related to NSFW for overlaying. The example images do not use Lora related to NSFW, but overlaying any of them will significantly improve the quality.

This series of models was generated with the default HI-RES setting, and I am not sure how much the image quality would be affected without it. However, based on the images generated by others in the discussion area without HI-RES, the results seem to be good.

I will not upload more example images because the style is very diverse, combining more than 50 models, including some realistic style images created by others in the discussion area.

items.name: Yusa Emi (Hataraku Maou-sama!)
items.description:
This is a character LoRA for Yusa Emi from Hataraku Maou-sama!.

This LoRA is trained with 21 handpicked images from gelbooru, zerochan, and pixiv on Anything v4.5.

To use this LoRA, include the trigger word yusaEmi at a weight of around 0.85-1. No other descriptive words should be necessary!
Generating her uniform can be a little tricky, but I find that including white shirt, long sleeves, bowtie, vest, and plaid pencil skirt with pencil and pen added to the negative prompts seem to have the most consistency.

I'm looking forward to see what you all come up with. Be sure to leave feedback as comments and reviews!

items.name: Camilla FE
items.description:
1st try at a LORA. Used the kohya LORA collab to make this Camilla LORA.

The different versions are from different epochs. I personally recommend 03, but I have noticed 04 can work better on more realistic / semirealistic models.

I recommend keeping the strength below 0.8, especially if you use the 04 version. It's gonna vary from model to model, and whether you are trying to get an image that is similar to Camilla or extremely similar.

Known issues:

  • Hands have a tendency to be raised and holding her hair or have 1 hand up and another down

  • Eye color doesnt always come out purple

  • Her horn crown shows up usually at higher values if you don't include fake horns in the negative

  • Back views are kind of sus because no training pics were from behind

  • Some models / LORAs you may need to specify a hair over one eye tag for consistency (especially face LORAs, like an ahegao one)

  • I've found if you don't add things to the prompt about her curves (eg: curvy, cleavage, breasts, large breasts, thick thighs, etc) in some models you get very un-camilla looking results

eg: adding just 2 descriptors about Camilla radically changed this result

Training data info:

  • Sample consisted of 52 images

  • tags were set manually

  • Model used to train was anything v3.0 w/ the anime.vae

Other embeddings / models / LORA etc used in example imgs:

  • nerfgun - bad prompt

  • yesyeahvh - bad hands 5

  • Ulzzang-6500

  • bloodsuga - perfect world (baked vae)

  • anything v3

  • anything v4.5

items.name: Cornelia li Britannia - Code Geass
items.description:
Another retrain. Did a lot of cleaning up and had to source some extra images for her secondary outfit. Ended up doing some Img2img to some settei images as they were too crappy and low resolution which rather inflated the training time. Regardless one cute Cornelia makes the effort worth it I guess. I stopped mid baking to test the LOCON version which is why that came out first. I normally put LOCONs first on the queue as they are more sensitive and if i screwed up they show it very easily. Regardless Let's get to the important bits.

V2:

Works fine with: <lora:cornelia_li_britanniaV2:0.7> cornelia_li_britannia,

The outfits I managed to isolate are:

  • cornelia_military_uniform: Her classic attire.

  • cornelia_white_cape: Her weird cape that goes with her classic attire.

  • white_bodysuit_red_bustier_red_gloves_red_thigh_boots: her secondary casual attire. I lightly trained her other cape but YMMV is is just tagged as cape.

As Always I will upload the tag summary with the dataset for people to experiment.

V1:

Another quality waifu. I am trying to focus on side characters as the most popular ones will inevitably be picked by someone else.

I got good results with: <lora:Cornelia_li_Britannia:0.6> Cornelia_li_Britannia, 1girl, big_breasts, purple_eyes, (lipstick:.9), (makeup:.8)

It seems in this case a lower CFG turned out better and ended up using 6.

Note: I think she has mole in roughly 25% of the training data so you might get it if you add the tag.

items.name: Boobs in bed
items.description:
Trained on 20 pictures of mostly naked women with large breasts laying down in bed. This model works best when provided with an input image. It can be hit or miss when using plain text-to-image.

Technical: Prompts can be anything you like and do not have to include "bed." I suggest starting off with my 512x512 example images as your input to get the ball rolling. 80% of training data was light-skinned woman, 20% dark-skinned, so you will have better quality when generating lighter skinned women.

Bad Generations? Specifying the desired ethnicity is helpful, especially for darker skin tones. If nipples are missing, describe them more in prompt. If areolas are weird shapes, use better input image or add "round areolas" to prompt. If eyes are on nipples, specify "eyes on nipples" or "eyes on breasts" in negative prompt.

It is good at making:

  • Women with huge boobs

  • Large areolas

  • Women with smaller boobs (with proper image input)

It is bad at/untrained for making:

  • Perfect fingers

  • Multiple women

  • Very different angles than top-down

  • Whole bodies

Example positive prompts: naked woman laying down, lying down, large breasts, round areolas

Example negative prompts: extra breasts, extra nipples, clothes, glasses (if applicable)

    • DPM++ Series(SDE Karras, 2M Karras, etc.)

    • about 20 steps, CFG scale 3.5~6.5

    • kl-f8-anime2.vae

    • CLIP skip = 1

    • If using highres

      • Latent series

      • Denoising strength 0.50~0.65

LoRA training info

  • trained on sd-scripts by kohya_ss. Thank you a lot!

  • based on Animefull-pruned

  • 162 images of mr. c.b.

    • 4x low quality 46 images

    • 8x medium quality 71 images

    • 16x high quality 45 images

    • => 1 epoch = 1472 images

  • replaced character feature tags with mr. c.b. \(umamusume\)

    • horse girl, horse tail, brown hair, blue eyes, etc.

  • using aspect ratio bucketing

  • resolution : 768x768

  • rank=alpha=16

  • using dadaptation

  • batch size = 4, 3 epochs trained

  • clip skip = 1

This LoRA may be compatible with animefull-based models (ex. AbyssOrangeMix Series...)

All uploaded images are generated by AOM3A1

Inpaint guide: if face on full body shots comes out deformed\not detailed enough - it's easily fixed with single inpaint, whole process takes half a minute. Press "Send to inpaint" button under generated image, mask the face area with drawing tool, choose DDIM sampler, set "Inpaint area" to "only masked", and set denoising strength to 0,5. Press generate and you done!

Review and comment with your experiences, I would appreciate whatever feedback you can provide in order to continue improving my technique.

items.name: Keqing
items.description:
Description

Trained on 119 images handpicked from booru/pixiv using AbyssOrangeMix2_sfw.

Usage

The weight can vary a lot depending on the model you're using and/or the composition you're going for, but it's usually best between 0.4~0.8. Tested on AOM2 but works well on anythingv3, anythingv4.5, elysium_anime_v3, etc.

The main trigger word is keqing. It has a weak association with her uniform, which means it can easily be replaced by something else (like in the examples).

Uniforms

If you use keqing_base_uniform, it will render her base uniform. If you use keqing_opulent_uniform, it will render her opulent splendor skin.
